Plot mask at coords (49)
#Parent OS_SpriteOp_Reason
=>	R0 =	<49, &31=>os_spriteop_reason2> (Plot mask at coords)
	R1 =	<Sprite area=>os_spriteop_area>
	R2 =	Sprite name/pointer
	R3 =	x coordinate
	R4 =	y coordinate

This plots the solid pixels in the background colour with the bottom left corner at the given coordinates. 
